ISLAMABAD, Aug 09 (APP): The Power Division on Friday clarified a news item appeared in a section of press about increase in power tariff by Rs 2.56 per unit and said that with this fuel cost notification consumers have got a relief of Rs 0.77 as compared to the last month.
â€œThe Power Division makes clarification for public information about News items published in various newspapers dated August 9th 2024, claiming that the government has increased electricity tariffs by Rs. 2.56 per unit whereas there has been reduction in rates as compared to last month bills, said a clarification issued here by the Power Division.
